The paper discusses Multiagent Systems (MAS) and their adaptation to the highly dynamic environments of the Internet of Things (IoT) and Autonomous Vehicles. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses governance, which is a key feature of MAS coordination, organizations, and institutions. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses challenges and future directions for the development of domain-specific smart IoT systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
